    {
      "id": "a7f8f0ba7ace1133691c5aa6437b187a90fa7a15",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-05 23:45:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAdding these extra 1 second delay bits seems to be very time wasting thing, I wonder if there is any better/lightweight  way to fix it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fbffcbe5ad434f1f1c3af58509abd766a90dedfe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-06 01:58:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Adding these extra 1 second delay bits seems to be very time wasting thing, I wonder if there is any better/lightweight way to fix it?\n\nIn fact, for each PDO test, the fail_loc flag of \"OBD_FAIL_MDS_PDO_LOCK\" will block the OP1 at least 10s, and plus another 1s sleep before such blocking in the scripts, so increasing another 1s latency is not much time wasting.\n\nOn the other hand, the race between the two operations are mainly caused by client-side CPU schedule. It is not easy and unreasonable to make OP2 must finished after OP1, otherwise we cannot detect the real PDO test failure.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c69bcdea3ec4d6f9f85066aedbd4a73166328ff4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-06 18:17:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nYou are right and we fixed that in orion branch but in simpler way, just put sleep 1 inside check_pdo_conflict:\n\ncheck_pdo_conflict()\n\tlocal conflict=0\n+\tsleep 1\n\tif [[ `ps --pid $pid | wc -l` == 1 ]]; then\n\nI'd like this to be the same in both branches, so set -1 unless you have good reasons to prefer your way.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3a77c5e675aaf56a4e1e12c1b6f99a16cef15bd9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-07 02:42:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>You are right and we fixed that in orion branch but in simpler way, just put sleep 1 inside check_pdo_conflict:\n>check_pdo_conflict()\n>\tlocal conflict=0\n>+\tsleep 1\n>\tif [[ `ps --pid $pid | wc -l` == 1 ]]; then\n>I'd like this to be the same in both branches, so set -1 unless you have good reasons to prefer your way.\n\nI have thought to fix as you said before. But I did not fix as that because for sanityn test_40a - test_40e, the OP1 should not block OP2, such 1 sec sleep is unnecessary for them.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
